Company Overview of Stone Ridge Trust - Stone Ridge High Yield Reinsurance Risk Premium Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Stone Ridge Trust - Stone Ridge High Yield Reinsurance Risk Premium Fund is an open-ended balanced mutual fund launched and managed by Stone Ridge Asset Management LLC. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. For its equity portion, the fund invests directly and through derivatives such as swaps in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the stocks of companies operating across all market capitalizations. For its fixed income portion, the fund invests in high yield reinsurance-related securities which are rated lower than Baa3 by Moody’s Investors Service, Inc. and lower than BBB- by S&P and are of any maturity. It em...
Stone Ridge Trust - Stone Ridge High Yield Reinsurance Risk Premium Fund is an open-ended balanced mutual fund launched and managed by Stone Ridge Asset Management LLC. It invests in the public equity and fixed income markets of the United States. For its equity portion, the fund invests directly and through derivatives such as swaps in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the stocks of companies operating across all market capitalizations. For its fixed income portion, the fund invests in high yield reinsurance-related securities which are rated lower than Baa3 by Moody’s Investors Service, Inc. and lower than BBB- by S&P and are of any maturity. It employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis with a focus on factors such as trigger transparency, sponsor basis risk, call provisions, moral hazard, and correlation with other investments to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the BofA Merrill Lynch 3-Month U.S. Treasury Bill Index. Stone Ridge Trust - Stone Ridge High Yield Reinsurance Risk Premium Fund was formed on February 1, 2013 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


